summarization of the company’s business strategy – swot analysis – a detailed analysis of the company’s strengths weakness opportunities and threats – company history – progression of key events associated with the company – major products and services – a list of major products services and brands of the company – key competitors – a list of key competitors to the company – key employees – a list of the key executives of the company – executive biographies – a brief summary of the executives’ employment history – key operational heads – a list of personnel heading key departmentsfunctions – important locations and subsidiaries – a list of key locations and subsidiaries of the company including contact details highlights pepco holdings llc pepco holdings a subsidiary of exelon corporation is a utility services holding company that transmits distributes and supplies electricity through its subsidiaries it also distributes and supplies natural gas the company through its subsidiary also operates energy savings performance contracting business thermal business and an underground transmission and distribution construction business the company offers its services to residential commercial and industrial customers it supplies electricity in delaware columbia maryland alabama and new jersey and gas in delaware pepco holdings is headquartered in washington the us pepco holdings llc key recent developments sep   maryland utilities issue request for proposals for the supply of wholesale electric power apr   pepco files for rate adjustment to support reliability and technology investments feb   pepco holdings reports fourth quarter and full year  financial results oct   pepco holdings reports third quarter  financial results oct   pepco issues rfp for wholesale electric power for dc customers reasons to buy – gain key insights into the company for academic or business research purposes key elements such as swot analysis and corporate strategy are incorporated in the profile to